#- §oPreamble to the Prussian Constitution §r
We, the Prussians, wish to live peacefully among Civcraft, without aggression from an outside source. We wish to establish positive foreign with
not only the Jacks, but with all of the powers of Civcraft.
#- The Prussian Community, as it stands, is a non-violent entity, which wishes nothing but good relations with everyone, as we hope to establish a presence on the server. We hope to go public and bring with us a new, unique, and elegant city filled with 
#- all members of Civcraft, and not just the private enclave, which we have been involuntarily subjected.
§r
While we are aware that the Jacks do not appreciate our presence on the server, we implore them, and others, to
#- reconsider and recognize new beginnings as the Prussian Community develops and eventually becomes an established state on Civcraft.
#- §l     Prussian
§l   Constitution
§n_ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _
§r
Prussia is a souvereign state on the CivCraft-Server. The System is Constitutional Monarchist. The state Languages are English and German. The Flag and National Anthem
#- are those of historic Prussia.
§r
The Capital of Prussia is Danzig. The End residence is Marienburg. Plots in Danzig and rooms in Marienburg are free and cannot be sold or paid. Instead, non-
prussians have to pay a security deposit
#- of 1i per four blocks plot size. In order to construct a building, the Building rules on the Subreddit "civcraftprussia" have to be read and followed.
§r
Prussia has two mottos:
#- Historical:
"§oJedem das Seine§r"
(to each what he deserves)
§r
Civcraftian:
"§oOrdnung. Ehre. Freiheit.§r"
(Order. Honor. Freedom.)
#- Any person who finds a Loophole in this Constitution and tries to exploit it will be officially called a dickhead and the Loophole will be fixed and all profits of the person reclaimed.
§r
Prussian Flag, Anthem:
bit.ly/Qvgjwv
bit.ly/Ms98c0
#- §lSection 1:
Ranks of Prussians
§r
§o1st Rank:
King of Prussia
§r
The King of Prussia is a chicken named Uncle Dolan. All obey to anything it says.
#- §o2nd Rank:
Member of Parliament
§r
Members of Parliament are the Government of Prussia. Members without a specific role other than voting on state affairs are referred to as "Senator", all others are "Minister". People 
#- can be multiple Ministers at once, also There can be Ministries without a Minister, if there is noone willing and capable to do it.
§r
The Parliament will be elected by the people upon the foundation of the state. After this, the Ministers
#- nominate their successors. If more than half of the Citiziens want that a Senator or Minister resigns, he has to do so. If this happens, or a Minister or Senator resigns without nominating a Successor, the Parliament votes on
#- the Successor.
§r
Prussian Citiziens have to obey any member of the Parliament. If a Citizien thinks, that an order is unjustified or not necessary he can insist on the voice of a second Member of the parliament. Orders may include the
#- gathering of resources, the deliverance of goods or help in constructing a communal Building or Machine. This may not be used by Ministers to gain personal profit.
#- There will be the following Ministers:
§r
-Minister of Ordnung,
He gives out access to the community chests and coordinates Storage systems.
§r
-Minister of the Vault, He is in charge of finance.
#- -Minister of Diplomacy, He has the duty to build an Embassy in every friendly State and to stay in Contact to establish trade and positive relations.
§r
-Minister of Infrastructure, He coordinates the building of streets and railyways in and
#- between settlments, as well as the distribution of Plots to the citiziens.
§r
-Minister of Building,
He is responsible for the Coordination of public Buildings and the Homogenity of the Houses in Prussian settlements.
#- -Minister of Resources, He is responsible for the Claiming of Resources and for the Compensation Work of Prisoners.
§r
-Minister of Defence, In case of war or other major attack on Prussia, the King nominates him as
#- the General of the Prussian troops. If there is no war, the Minister of Defence is anormal Senator or Minister of another Domain.

#- §o3rd Rank:
Prussian Citizien
§r
A Citizien is a Resident of a Prussian Settlement. He has the Right to build one House and one shop on the marked plot in each Settlement. He has the Right to access the community chests, but also the
#- Duty to donate unneeded Material and to assist the Minister of Resources. He can't be a Member of another state.
§o
4th Rank:
Honorary Citizien
§r
Despite being the lowest rank of
#- Prussians, Honorary Citiziens have nearly the same rights as Prussian Citiziens. They have access to Community Chests and the right to build one single House and One single shop in one single Prussian Settlement. They have no duties regarding
#- Prussia and can be Members of another state.
§r
#- §lSection 2:
§lDiplomacy
§r
Prussia's Main goal in Diplomacy is to establish peaceful Connections to all other Nations, as well as to fight against Thieves and Griefers in the Overworld and to reform them in the End. Newbies and
#- Travellers will get food and shelter, everyone who lives peacefully can rely on a warm welcome in any Prussian Settlement.
§r
Prussia accepts every religion on the server as long as the majority of the followers are
#- peaceful and don't force their beliefs on others. Every religion has the right to build a shrine in the designated areas of the Cathedral of Danzig.
§r
The following Paragraphs determine, what happens when Individuals or
#- States are aggressive against the state of Prussia, Prussians or their property.
#- §lSection 2.1:
Diplomacy with Individuals
§r
Everyone is welcome in every Prussian Settlement. There are however certain rules that have to be respected.
§r
A trespasser will be
Pearled if:
#- -He attempts to destroy or grief property of Prussia or that of one of its Citiziens
§r
-He walks into private areas and doesn't make an attempt to leave after being told twice.
§r

#- -He attacks a Prussian anywhere or a peaceful Visitor on Prussian Ground
§r
-He clearly states in Mumble, ingame chat, reddit or via any other media, that he intends to do one of the above
#- Items of pearled criminals will be held in a locked chest and returned on release except stolen Goods and Compensation for damaged Individuals. Every Damage done to Prussian Property cannot be paid, but has to be worked off. Instead of normal arbitration,
#- the Prussian State can decide to lead the criminal to Endheim and give him a double chest and a diamond to lock it. He has to farm an amount of goods equivalent to the damage done (the Parliament decides on the amount and type of resources) and is freed
#- after the goods are delivered.
§r
The Parliament can set a "Minimum End time". If the goods are delivered before this time is over, the Parliament will decide if they want to free the prisoner yet or not. If the Parliament decides to do so,
#- the Prisoner will be freed instantly. If not, he can be compensated with six iron and one diamond a day, to show appreciation of his remorse/efforts if any. Prisoners that are freed can decide to stay in the end until the Minimum End Time is over to do
#- paid work for Prussia or to just stay a bit longer for whatever reason.
§r
If a Member of the Prussian State breaks other States' laws of griefs, steals or murders a Stateless individual, he has the Right to get a Process in Prussia where he
#- is ruled with Prussian Law. The Parliament has the right to exile anyone at any time for mischeivious behavious, thus denying this Right to anyone deemed untrustworthy.
#- §lSection 2.2
Diplomacy with States
§r
Prussia respects and accepts every foreign Law on the Server, as long as it follows the Non-Aggression-
Principle. Every State has the possibility to build an Embassy in the Prussian Capital.
#- If an Individual acts on behalf of a State or Group while breaking Prussian Law, the Parliament can decide to declare a War against this State or Group. The Parliament has to check if the malicious actions were really ordered by a government before
#- declaring a war. Prisoners of war are arbitrated personally, depending on the war-crimes they committed and their ranks in the State.
§r
In Times of War or Danger every Prussian has the duty to wear his best armor at all times. In times
#- of peace he shall wear no more than enchanted iron or unenchanted diamond armor, unless he intends to travel through dangerous land. A Prussian has the right to carry any Sword at any time, but is encouraged to set the same standards as his armor.
#- §lSection 3: Endheim
§r
Prussia will maintain Endheim as a Working Camp for Griefers and other Criminals to give them a possibility to show good behaviour and to compensate for damages done. Upon arrival, new inmates are put on the "Suspicious-List", If 
#- they behave they are removed, If they tend to continue with criminal actions in the End they are put on the "Kill-on-Sight List" and are denied access to Endheim or Marienburg.
§r
Marienburg is a settlement with the purpose of re-
#- stocking Endheim in case of griefing and to be a safe harbor for pearled Prussians. Marienburg buys Resources from Prisoners in exchange of rarer goods. Marienburg does not sell weapons and armament to prisoners. Endheim is no Prussian Ground,
#- but as long as a Prussian is Mayor of Endheim, Prussian Laws apply. Marienburg Is Prussian Ground.
#- §lSection 4:
How to become a Prussian
§r
Everyone can become a Prussian, as long as he agrees to our laws and accepts the Prussian Virtues as guide to Life in Civcraft. Any Senator or Minister can give the Prussian
#- Citizienship to people deemed worthy.
§r
The Parliament can nominate Honorary Prussians for their deeds for Prussia.
#- 